[[Image:Winter_sun_on_Norwegian_mountain.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A mountain (large mass of rock)]]

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|muntaine|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|VL.}} {{recons|montanea|montānea|lang=VL.}}, feminine of *{{term||montāneus|mountainous}}, alteration of {{etyl|la}} {{term|montanus|montānus|lang=la}}, from {{term|mons|mōns||mountain|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|monti}} (compare Welsh {{term|mynydd||mountain|lang=cy}}, Albanian {{term|mat||bank, shore|lang=sq}}, Avestan {{rfscript|Avestan}} {{term||tr=mati||promontory|lang=ae}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|men-|to project, stick out}}. More at [[menace]].

